rComments: She's a wonderful prof. I found the course material eye-opening and super interesting. There's quite a bit of group work and readings to do, but it was a great experience to learn how to work and collaborate with others since that's what every job out there requires us to do.

Overall, Arellano is an alright prof. There was a group assignment, a midterm, a group presentation, a participation mark, and a final. The midterm was very difficult while the other assignments weren't too bad. Still, I found it hard to get a good grade in this class. Also, the second half of the class was guest speakers which I really enjoyed!
Amazing professor! I learned so much in her course!

Class lacks content and organization,  and you will be bored, although it is a very easy A. But the downside is that you will not get any feedback on your work as Prof. Allerano is not organized and will not hand back marked papers no matter how many time she promises to do so (im sure we have all ran into the type before).

Fairly easy course, midterm and exam straight forward.  Easy 10/10 with in class cases.  She can be difficult to understand with her accent and quiet speech.  She was nice enough to give me a 80 in the course when I got a 79.
